Every research project is unique and students must build
dedicated tools to perform their research (code, datasets).
Those are not trivial to manage, share, publish, but embeded
into the aformentioned Knowledge base, they can be linked
and have the potential to fit all the guidelines set by the
Open Science community as well as becoming interactif.
I found a method to maximize the value from my scientifc work by
making it open, accessible online and following the FAIR principles.
To achieve that, I used a bundle of Open-Source softwares, and l
ots of ressources I found on the internet (and lots of trial and error).
What I can offer from having been through this journey is:
Ressources, Tutorials, Adivises, Counceling, Templates and Ideas ...
... to anyone that wishes to follow my path. My main target are PhD
students as it is part of their job to find a suitable method to do
research, and there is no tools to implement the scientific method.
Self-publishing is an alternative to commercial scientific publication.
Every researcher is concerned with this problematic and may
embrace the opportunity to step away from it.
